
logrotate - easy administation of systems, generate large number of log files.
logrotate allows automatic rotation, removal, compression and mailing of log files.
Using logrotate we can store logs longer with a less disk space, we can handle logs daily, weekly, monthly etc

/etc/logrotate.conf - logrotate config file

#--------------ADDING CONFIGURATION----------------
sudo nano /etc/logrotate.d/example-app

/var/log/example-app/*.log {
daily
missingok
rotate 14
compress
notifempty
create 0640 www-data www-data	#after rotation, this will create a new empty log file and specify permissions 
sharedscripts			#config script runs only once per run
postrotate			
systemctl reload example-app
endscript
}

sudo logrotate /etc/logrotate.conf --debug	#customize config file based upon our needs
